{
  "texts": [
    "However, their ability to understand context and nuance in text is unparalleled.",
    "Thus, the choice of feature extraction method significantly impacts the computational efficiency and effectiveness of SR automation.",
    "While traditional methods like BoW and TF-IDF are computationally less demanding and thus more prevalent in larger datasets, advanced methods like BERT provide superior contextual understanding, suggesting a trade-off between performance and computational overhead.",
    "Continuing with the NLP pipeline depicted in Fig. 2, the subsequent stage following text vectorisation is typically modelling.",
    "The three main AI learning models identified in the related works for SR automation include the rule-based approach, ML and DL, a subclass of ML (Song et al. 2020)."
  ]
}